[thinking] **Refining exception handling**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm considering how to handle exceptions more effectively in the JVM. If assertions fail inside a callable, it might be wrapped as a WrappedException instead of an Error, which will allow me to throw an exception. However, if native unsupported errors occur, I need to ensure those aren't wrapped. Catching Errors directly is still essential. I need to make these edits for improved clarity and functionality in the handling process.
